Constellation is a collection of utilities for .NET CMS implementers.
		The Foundation.Context namespace contains a contract for context-sensitive objects along with a context evaluator that compares
		the sensitive instances' runtime settings against their configured scope.

		The purpose of this library is to provide scoped pipeline handlers to Sitecore to prevent developers from unintentionally executing
		their customizations outside the scope of their current project/site/tenant/feature.

		Configured for use with Sitecore 9.0.
		Requires Sitecore 9.0 NuGet packages, available here: https://sitecore.myget.org/F/sc-packages/api/v3/index.json
summary: Sitecore Helix library to support context-aware pipeline, event and rule handlers.

[Minimal package for .NET 2.0] Wheel is a library to get started efficiently with .NET core and ASP.NET core projects.

Its comprehensive architecture, with many default configurations and tools, allows to focus directly on business-related code like you would do on a modern, high level framework, and promotes the reuse of code and concepts between different projects.

This package is intended for minimal command line applications that must run on obsolete platforms such as .NET Framework 2.0 and/or that does not need a connection to a database. It has support for Microsoft.Extensions.Configuration, Microsoft.Extensions.Logging and Microsoft.Extensions.DependencyInjection (not for .NET Framework 2.0), using NLog as the backend logging implementation.
      
For database-aware or web applications, see Wheel and Wheel.Web packages.
